body:
This commit creates a firehose that can connect to conjurer directly. There are also changes created in the Conjure repository (You can see the forked conjure repo here:  https://github.com/dhruvp/d8a-conjure/tree/cardinalitySpecifications). Here's the pull request: https://github.com/housejester/d8a-conjure/pull/4
 In particularly, one can now specify a set of cardinalities, types, columns, and metrics to be conjured. An example specification might look like:

{
   "columns":10,
   "cardinalityRequirements":{
      "10":2, (Means 2 columns of cardinality 10)
      "1":2,
      "100":1
   },
   "typeRequirements":{
       "string":2, (2 string columns)
       "double":2
   },
   "aggregators":[],
   "defaultCardinality":10,
   "defaultType":"int",
   "special column list": [ (Allows you to create custom columns as well)
       {
           "name":"Producers",
           "cardinality": 5,
           "type": "string"
       }
   ]
}

order by with one or more metrics in ascending or descending order;
limit returned result
having clause with logic operators. No custom aggregation function yet.
